# Line-ending policy — committed so behavior does NOT depend on each machine's
# core.autocrlf (the Git-for-Windows default, =true, produced phantom "modified"
# churn on this Windows/OneDrive checkout: checkout wrote CRLF, but tools/OneDrive
# rewrote LF, so files showed as modified with an empty content diff).
#
# The repo is already LF-in-blob; this keeps working trees LF too. LF is required
# for the bash hooks/scripts and is conventional for Node. Git auto-detects text
# vs binary; eol=lf applies to detected text files only.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit binaries — never normalize EOL, never text-diff.
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.ico  binary
*.pdf  binary
*.tgz  binary
